@@
 ## Development
 
 ```bash
 go mod tidy
 go run ./cmd/caracal-software-installer
+make build
 ```
@@
 The app looks for installer scripts in:
@@
 Most package installs write to `/opt`, `/usr/local`, or the current user's home directory so they work on an atomic Caracal system without rpm layering.
+
+## Build And Install
+
+```bash
+make build
+make test
+make validate
+sudo make install
+```
+
+This installs:
+
+- `caracal-software-installer` to `/usr/bin`
+- `caracal-download-index` to `/usr/libexec/caracal-software-installer`
+- shell installer scripts to `/usr/lib/caracal-software-installer/scripts`
+- `download-index.csv` to `/usr/lib/caracal-software-installer/data`
+- `logo.txt` and image assets to `/usr/share/caracal-software-installer`
+
+For packaging, use `DESTDIR` and `PREFIX` as needed, for example `make install DESTDIR="$pkgdir" PREFIX=/usr`.
